I suppose this is as good a place as any to ask about a problem with my
mill.  I'm trying to motorize it, which means getting the handle off.  It
looks like a hole was drilled into the rod directly turning the roller, as
well as a hole drilled into the handle.  From what I can tell, two bolts
were screwed down to secure it.  The head diameter of the bolts allow them
to go all the way down to the bottom--I assume there's a special name for
them but I wouldn't know.

Of course the first one comes out, but the second doesn't.  Or I dunno
what's really happening since it's impossible to get a good view in down
there.  It was suggested I try an extractor tool; drill into the piece,
hammer that in, and I should be able to unscrew everything.  This didn't
work, and seems to have screwed up the holes enough that I think my only
solution is to just drill drill away until the handle separates.

Do any of you know if there's anything else that could be securing the
handle in?  At this point, I can clamp the roller's rod and then roughly
twist the handle around it 3/4 of the way.  It's flat on one side BTW,
which the handle is held in place by a completely round hole.  I don't know
what to do to get the thing off.
